# ============================================
# .docker-env-chain — the ROOT project-level env chain (Layer 1).
#
# These are the files that drive ${VAR} interpolation in the root + included
# compose YAML. ${ENV} (a.k.a. ${COMPOSE_ENV}) resolves as shell COMPOSE_ENV >
# .env COMPOSE_ENV > "dev". Missing files are silently skipped. Last wins.
#
# Subproject service env_file: paths (web/.web.env, api/.api.env) are NOT listed
# here — they are AUTO-DISCOVERED (Layer 2) from the included subproject compose
# files to COMPOSE_DEPTH levels (default 3). That cross-subproject discovery is
# what lets a ${WEB_PORT} declared only in web/.web.env resolve from the root.
# ============================================

# Layer 1: root base + env-specific overlay
.env
.${ENV}.env

# Layer 2 here = SECRETS only (last wins, gitignored). Per-subproject secrets
# live in each subproject's own gitignored env file (e.g. web/.web.secrets.env)
# and are discovered via that subproject's env_file: — keep them out of root.
.secrets.env
